## 10. Preprocess Output Summary

### Main Visual Character

Bosco Verticale presents a high-rise residential tower as a vertical forest. Its image is defined by dense balcony vegetation, seasonal facade transformation, and the contrast between urban density and natural growth.

### Main Atmospheric Quality

The project creates a green, layered, and ecological atmosphere. It softens the typical high-rise residential image and gives the tower a strong relationship with nature.

### Main Design Reading

The project uses vegetation not as decoration but as an architectural system. The facade becomes a living environmental layer that supports shade, privacy, biodiversity, and urban identity.

